Text.Value: I must say, if this is a practical joke, it is not very amusing.
Oh, how lovely, our visitors return! We were just about to try some of Master Meztli's delightful wines. Would you care to join us?
They do look ever so tasty.
That wine is poisonous, Cora. This man is trying to kill you.
Ah, Mrs Highberry, I prefer to conduct tastings individually, so I may assess your palate -
Poison... Beauteous... Sickly... Delicate.
This fiend has sullied good wine with poison!
I was in business for a great many years, Master Meztli, and my wife, as always, is most correct.
I'm afraid I must decline, but I hope you enjoy your wine.
Who on earth is 'Dolor'?
No...
Call me Cora, Master Meztli. And I'm afraid I must insist on their joining us - wine's no good without company, after all!
I've smelled many a wine in my time, and this one's foul. Poisonous.
Cora Highberry, your life is in danger. A serial killer is after you.
Why, hello there! We were just about to try some of Master Meztli's delightful wines. Would you care to join us?
Kill the poisoner. One death is as good as another.
Attack the poisoner.
Then please, Mrs Highberry, lead the toast.
